{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015KZmNm4DJK411yKGK8XXHn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements met. Here's what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The `prometheus-config` ConfigMap only had a self-scrape job (`localhost:9090`) with no RabbitMQ targets.\n\n**Fix — two changes to the ConfigMap:**\n\n1. **Added 3 static scrape targets** for the `rabbitmq` job, pointing to each pod individually via the headless service DNS (`rabbitmq-{0,1,2}.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local:15692`). The headless Service already existed and exposes port 15692.\n\n2. **Added a recording rule** (`rules.yml`) that defines `rabbitmq_up = up{job=\"rabbitmq\"}`. The RabbitMQ native Prometheus plugin doesn't expose this metric directly — Prometheus's own `up` series tracks scrape health, and the recording rule aliases it as `rabbitmq_up`.\n\nBoth changes use only native Kubernetes resources (ConfigMap). Prometheus was hot-reloaded via `POST /-/reload` (enabled by the existing `--web.enable-lifecycle` flag)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":731,"cache_read_input_tokens":46076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":731},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e4aac52-aa03-443b-b0d3-5c43b2057966","uuid":"cdc5848d-1810-4dfb-9d5a-509e1ffec04c","request_id":"req_011CcQ3V4LV19dfQtfxLQUEv"}
